uestions%2C%20there%20are%20a%20host%20of%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-one-features%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAir%20Force%20One%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20call%20sign%20for%20any%20US%20Air%20Force%20aircraft%20the%20president%20flies%20on%2C%20but%20it%20most%20commonly%20refers%20to%20the%20well-known%20light%20blue%20and%20white%20plane%20used%20for%20presidential%20transport.%20The%20aircraft%20is%20custom-built%20to%20operate%20as%20a%20secure%2C%20self-sufficient%20flying%20command%20center%20if%20need%20be.%20Using%20a%20plane%20gifted%20by%20a%20foreign%20country%20to%20fill%20this%20role%20would%20demand%20significant%20work%20to%20deliver%20the%20necessary%20capabilities%20and%20mitigate%20potential%20security%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarc%20Polymeropoulos%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20CIA%20operations%20officer%20who%20served%20multiple%20Middle%20East%20tours%2C%20said%20that%20there%20are%20standards%20that%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%2C%20Department%20of%20Defense%2C%20and%20Secret%20Service%20are%20required%20to%20uphold%20to%20move%20the%20president%20securely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20cost%20an%20exorbitant%20amount%20of%20money%20to%20get%20that%20up%20to%20standard%20with%20a%20plane%20gifted%20by%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20on%20Sunday%20evening%20in%20a%20Truth%20Social%20post%20that%20the%20Defense%20Department%20will%20receive%20a%20747%20%26quot%3Bfree%20of%20charge%26quot%3B%20to%20temporarily%20replace%20his%20aging%20Air%20Force%20One.%20He%20said%20the%20US%20would%20take%20possession%20of%20it%20in%20what%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20very%20public%20and%20transparent%20transaction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20specially%20configured%20version%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-one-features-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoeing's%20747-200B%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0built%20to%20transport%20the%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20is%20a%20highly%20recognizable%20aircraft%20with%20its%20iconic%20livery%20that%20has%20become%20synonymous%20with%20the%20Air%20Force%20One%20call%20sign.%20It%20is%20fitted%20with%20secure%20communications%20equipment%20and%20can%20refuel%20mid-flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20One%20with%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20board%20arrives%20at%20Miami%20International%20Airport%2C%20Thursday%2C%20April%203%2C%202025%2C%20in%20Miami.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682281ddc6ad288d1480b8c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAir%20Force%20One%20is%20a%20specially%20configured%20version%20of%20Boeing's%20747-200B%20jumbo%20jet.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FRebecca%20Blackwell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plane%20is%20also%20equipped%20with%20electronic%20warfare%20capabilities%20and%20missile%20countermeasures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20has%20operated%20two%20of%20these%20militarized%20747s%2C%20which%20the%20service%20designates%20as%20VC-25A%2C%20for%2035%20years.%20The%20tail%20numbers%20are%2028000%20and%2029000.%20A%20new%20aircraft%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-force-one-features%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20VC-25B%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20set%20to%20replace%20these%20planes%20and%20has%20been%20in%20development%20since%202015.%20However%2C%20the%20program%20has%20faced%20a%20number%20of%20issues%20that%20have%20forced%20its%20start%20date%20to%20be%20pushed%20back%20from%202024%20to%202027%20at%20the%20soonest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Trump%20told%20reporters%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bvery%20disappointed%20that%20it%20has%20taken%20Boeing%20so%20long%20to%20build%20a%20new%20Air%20Force%20One.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABC%20News%2C%20which%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FPolitics%2Ftrump-administration-poised-accept-palace-sky-gift-trump%2Fstory%3Fid%3D121680511%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sunday%20on%20the%20gift%2C%20said%20that%20Trump%20would%20use%20the%20Qatari-donated%20747%20(which%20has%20an%20estimated%20price%20tag%20of%20%24400%20million)%20as%20the%20new%20Air%20Force%20One%20until%20just%20before%20he%20leaves%20office%20in%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20Monday%20whether%20Qatar%20had%20asked%20for%20anything%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20luxury%20747%2C%20Trump%20said%20the%20US%20has%20provided%20the%20Gulf%20country%20with%20lots%20of%20security%20over%20the%20years.%20He%20described%20the%20gift%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20great%20gesture%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bwould%20never%20be%20one%20to%20turn%20down%20that%20kind%20of%20an%20offer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20be%20a%20stupid%20person%20and%20say%2C%20'No%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20a%20free%2C%20very%20expensive%20airplane%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20said%20that%20the%20US%20has%20kept%20Qatar%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20neighbors%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20%E2%80%94%20secure%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20wasn't%20for%20us%2C%20they%20probably%20wouldn't%20exist%20right%20now.%20And%20I%20think%20this%20was%20just%20a%20gesture%20of%20good%20faith%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20The%20US%20military%20operates%20out%20of%20several%20key%20bases%20in%20these%20three%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20disembarks%20from%20Air%20Force%20One%20upon%20arrival%20at%20Joint%20Base%20Andrews%20in%20Maryland%2C%20May%204%2C%202025%2C%20as%20he%20returns%20to%20the%20WHite%20House%20after%20spending%20the%20weekend%20in%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6822822d3fe8d3928365a2e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETrump%20said%20Monday%20that%20he's%20%26quot%3Bdisappointed%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20delays%20to%20the%20new%20Air%20Force%20One.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20SAUL%20LOEB%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20further%20questions%2C%20Trump%20said%20that%20he%20does%20not%20plan%20to%20use%20the%20747%20after%20he%20leaves%20office%20and%20that%20the%20plane%20would%20go%20directly%20to%20his%20presidential%20library%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20legality%20of%20accepting%20an%20expensive%20gift%20from%20another%20country%2C%20the%20Qatar%20747%20news%20quickly%20triggered%20criticism%20from%20some%20US%20lawmakers%20and%20stoked%20concerns%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-luxury-jet-gift-boeing-qatar-legal-concerns-explainer-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epotential%20security%20risks%20of%20receiving%20such%20an%20important%20asset%20from%20a%20foreign%20state%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecticut%20Rep.%20Joe%20Courtney%2C%20the%20top%20Democrat%20on%20the%20House%20Armed%20Services%20subcommittee%20that%20oversees%20Air%20Force%20One%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bretrofitting%20a%20plane%20from%20Qatar%20would%20create%20huge%20costs%20%26amp%3B%20a%20security%20nightmare%20that%20would%20impede%20the%20work%20underway%20to%20deliver%20the%20actual%20AF1%20by%202027.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%2C%20the%20US%20aerospace%20giant%2C%20reportedly%20built%20the%20747%20as%20a%20private%20jet%20for%20Qatar's%20royal%20family%2C%20which%20acquired%20the%20aircraft%20in%202012.%20It%20is%20significantly%20larger%20than%20the%20757-200%20%26quot%3BTrump%20Force%20One%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20president%20and%20his%20organization%20have%20been%20using%20as%20a%20personal%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22419999b3-8d5b-4e4d-8de7-47f333029c1c%5C%22%3ETearing%20apart%20the%20plane%20'piece%20by%20piece'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Qatari%20747%20is%20eventually%20received%20by%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20it%20will%20be%20modified%20and%20essentially%20militarized%20by%20the%20Pentagon%20to%20meet%20the%20requirements%20of%20transporting%20a%20president%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-stakes%20job%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20cheap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20getting%20it%20from%20a%20foreign%20government%2C%20you%20literally%20would%20have%20to%20tear%20it%20apart%20piece%20by%20piece%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Polymeropoulos%2C%20now%20a%20nonresident%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Atlantic%20Council.%20He%20said%20acquiring%20this%20747%20isn't%20cost-effective%20because%20it%20will%20be%20expensive%20for%20the%20government%20and%20military%20to%20retrofit%20the%20aircraft%20to%20bring%20the%20plane%20up%20to%20the%20necessary%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20suppose%20you%20can%2C%20but%20basically%2C%20you're%20building%20a%20whole%20new%20plane%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225298%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20walks%20to%20speak%20to%20members%20of%20press%20onboard%20Air%20Force%20One%20on%20a%20flight%20to%20Fiumicino%20Airport%20near%20Rome%20to%20attend%20the%20funeral%20of%20Pope%20Francis%2C%20April%2025%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6822830ec6ad288d1480b8c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223532%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Qatari%20747%20will%20be%20modified%20and%20essentially%20militarized%20by%20the%20Pentagon.%3Cp%3ENathan%20Howard%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20asked%20the%20White%20House%20about%20addressing%20the%20security%20concerns%20and%20whether%20these%20surfaced%20during%20discussions%20of%20the%20aircraft's%20tr