Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jenn%20Cho%20outdoors%20during%20her%20mental%20health%20leave.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681bd89dc6ad288d148054a0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EPhoto%20courtesy%20of%20Jenn%20Cho%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20hired%2027-year-old%20Jenny%20Cho%20right%20out%20of%20college.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECho%20said%20she%20instantly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-revamps-pay-structure-rewards-high-performing-employees-2025-5%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebecame%20a%20high%20achiever%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20completely%20burned%20out%20after%20five%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20taking%20a%20mental%20health%20leave%2C%20she%20switched%20her%20focus%20to%20trade-offs%20instead%20of%20balance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jenn%20Cho%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20Amazon%20software%20developer%20in%20Seattle.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20hired%20at%20Amazon%20directly%20out%20of%20college%20in%202019%20and%20made%20work%20my%20life%20and%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20so%20much%20pressure%20on%20myself%20to%20be%20a%20high%20achiever%20and%20to%20prove%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-best-candidate-might-not-have-relevant-experience-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20valuable%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20my%20early%20career.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20I%20had%20completely%20burned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20a%2012-week%20leave%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20mental%20health%20and%20realized%20my%20job%20wasn't%20the%20issue%2C%20it%20was%20my%20mindset.%20Here's%20how%20I%20identified%20my%20burnout%20and%20how%20I'm%20trying%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20happening%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2284dc2140-26ed-4770-9cb4-90aa0ccbabf2%5C%22%3EEverything%20was%20great%20for%20me%20until%20a%20stressful%20project%20in%202024%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20hired%20as%20a%20support%20engineer%2C%20my%20job%20was%20really%20exciting.%20We%20moved%20quickly%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20a%20sponge%2C%20absorbing%20everything%2C%20and%20craving%20to%20learn%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202024%2C%20Amazon%20entered%20a%20very%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-layoffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estressful%20layoff%20season%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20greatly%20affected%20my%20team.%20Our%20organization%20underwent%20a%20lot%20of%20restructuring%20and%20reprioritization%20of%20our%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20on%20a%20particularly%20difficult%20project%20and%20really%20put%20pressure%20on%20myself%20to%20be%20on%20point%20at%20all%20times.%20But%20in%20the%20pursuit%20of%20doubling%20down%20on%20work%20and%20working%20longer%20hours%2C%20I%20started%20lacking%20motivation%2C%20struggling%20with%20focus%2C%20and%20feeling%20emotionally%20exhausted.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20deadlines%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20in%20survival%20mode.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5be9197-1384-436e-8205-f8a56f44e456%5C%22%3EWhen%20I%20stopped%20enjoying%20my%20hobbies%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20burned%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wake-up%20call%20that%20something%20needed%20to%20change%20didn't%20come%20until%20I%20realized%20I%20wasn't%20even%20enjoying%20the%20things%20I%20love%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20working%20out%2C%20spending%20time%20with%20friends%2C%20pursuing%20hobbies.%20I%20knew%20I%20was%20burned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20friend%20of%20mine%20who%20had%20recently%20burned%20out%20and%20taken%20a%20leave%2C%20encouraged%20me%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etake%20my%20own%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20sitting%20on%20the%20idea%20for%20a%20while%2C%20I%20submitted%20a%20request%20with%20the%20support%20of%20my%20therapist%2C%20and%20I%20was%20approved%20for%20a%2012-week%20leave%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22988561c1-d278-4b49-95cf-da17cda59cc4%5C%22%3ETaking%20a%20break%20from%20work%20and%20building%20something%20for%20myself%20was%20fulfilling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20my%20leave%2C%20I%20broke%20out%20in%20full-body%20hives%2C%20which%20I%20suspect%20might've%20been%20stress-induced.%20After%20nearly%20six%20weeks%20of%20treating%20my%20health%20issues%2C%20I%20finally%20settled%20into%20my%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-to-do-in-seattle-washington%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexplored%20Seattle%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20got%20back%20into%20my%20workout%20routine%2C%20and%20even%20started%20working%20on%20some%20personal%20projects%20like%20a%20food%20blog%20site.%20It%20was%20so%20fulfilling%20to%20build%20something%20for%20myself.%20I%20considered%20taking%20a%20sabbatical%20or%20a%20more%20extended%20leave%2C%20but%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20stick%20with%20my%2012-week%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20the%20biggest%20thing%20that%20needed%20to%20change%20when%20I%20was%20to%20return%20to%20Amazon%20was%20my%20mindset.%20Finding%20fulfillment%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-find-a-hobby-work-life-balance-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emy%20hobbies%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20me%20realize%20that%20work%20shouldn't%20be%20my%20life%3B%20it%20should%20fuel%20my%20ability%20to%20live%20my%20life%20and%20pursue%20my%20passions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da0889bf-73f5-4758-a35a-2b5057da5081%5C%22%3EWhen%20I%20got%20back%20from%20my%20leave%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20nothing%20had%20changed%2C%20and%20I%20needed%20to%20set%20boundaries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20concerned%20about%20taking%20a%20leave%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20hindered%20my%20career%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20returning%20to%20work%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20was%20just%20one%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees.%20The%20company%20doesn't%20stop%20just%20because%20one%20person%20leaves.%20As%20workers%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20prioritize%20work%2C%20but%20our%20employers%20prioritize%20profits%2C%20so%20it's%20up%20to%20us%20to%20create%20boundaries%20between%20work%20and%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20trying%20to%20embody%20my%20new%20mindset%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esetting%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20example%2C%20working%20out%20is%20crucial%20for%20my%20mental%20health%2C%20so%20I've%20set%20a%20boundary%20that%20I%20will%20not%20cancel%20a%20workout%20class%20to%20keep%20working.%20It's%20a%20hard%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20been%20writing%20down%20my%20to-do%20lists%20for%20the%20day%2C%20but%20not%20just%20making%20them%20centered%20on%20work.%20Sure%2C%20my%20work%20will%20be%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list%2C%20but%20I've%20also%20been%20writing%20down%20the%20personal%20things%20I'm%20looking%20forward%20to%20doing%20after%20work%2C%20like%20getting%20dinner%2C%20seeing%20friends%2C%20or%20working%20on%20the%20food%20blog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d86d15d-3112-4f83-a6ea-71cc8082175b%5C%22%3EI'm%20focusing%20on%20trade-offs%20instead%20of%20a%20balance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20day-to-day%20basis%2C%20it%20feels%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20find%20a%20balance%20between%20work%20and%20life.%20I%20have%20so%20many%20things%20I%20want%20to%20do%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20hours%20in%20the%20day.%20So%2C%20I'm%20looking%20at%20the%20bigger%20picture%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be